## Types of permissions for files and folders
Read (folder) - allows viewing and listening to files and subfolders 
Read (file) - allows viewing or accessing a file's contents 
Write (folder) - permits adding of files and subfolders
Write (file) - permits writing a file
Read and Execute (folder and file) - Same as read, but you can now execute 
Listen Folder Contents (folder only) - allows listening and viewing of files and subfolders as well as executing, but for subfolders only. 

